KOWLOON — delta port, Jhen River / Coppersalt Bay, continental north.
Lampkeepers (hermits tending beacons for strangers without payment) = seed of
civic neutrality.

FOUNDING: Three Ashfall Monsoon years drowned the delta. Year three: Yen-Mak
swallowed, 600 dead one night. Survivors forged the Neon Covenant on the one
basalt outcrop that never submerged, inked in phosphorescent squid dye (can't
alter it in darkness). Promises: one wall one law / one ledger one ration code
/ one square final judgment.

FIVE INSTITUTIONS (no one rules alone; each can censure the others):
- Harbor Syndics: docks, tariffs; intertwined with smuggling networks
- Jade Magistracy: civil law, rationing; jade seal requires two magistrates
  (no single-official emergency powers)
- Temple Circle: healing, funerary, sanctuary; no secular authority while
  treating patients (Covenant privilege)
- Wardens of Iron: walls, gate discipline; officers rotate seasonally
- Courier Lantern Office: registry, post, signal-lantern relay toward Midgaard;
  runners' brass badges pass any gate at any hour

COLORS: Crimson (emergency/execution). Jade (magistrate). Gold (merchants).
Blue (Harbor Syndic/docks). Violet (night markets). Cyan (flood indicators).

GATES: Jade (north). Iron (caravan). Lantern (west, travelers' lamps). Tide
(harbor).

EXECUTION SQUARE: over the covenant basalt; Executioner = constitutional office
(iron river-dragon mask); activated by tribunal seal for assassination in
sanctuary / gate sabotage / theft from reserves / riot during flood.

CURRENT TENSIONS:
- River Corsairs (Blacktide Shen): probes gate timings
- Salt Court Exiles (Duchess Yuen Ahi): debt rings, exploiting founding-house
  legal merger flaw
- Ash Cult: sabotages floodworks; popular support in lower wards
- Jade Eels: smuggling syndicate in Harbor Syndics; three investigations closed;
  believed to hold a Syndic seat

BLACK LEDGER: unredacted founding census with Conclave transfer names; rumored
in undercity cistern. Every faction would kill to find it.
